ogimage={srcImage.src}
>
    <div class="text-center">
        <MyH1 text="Best steelhead fishing spots near Beverton, Oregon" />
        <p class="mb-4">Comprehensive guide to best steelhead fishing hotspots – with seasonal tips, gear suggestions, and local insights.</p>

        <Image
            src={srcImage}
            alt="Best steelhead fishing spots near Beverton, Oregon"
            loading={"eager"}
            fetchpriority={"high"}
            class="rounded-xl shadow mx-auto"
            />
            <br>
    </div>

    <h3>
    1. <strong>Clackamas River</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Distance:</strong> ~30 min southeast of Beaverton
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Runs:</strong> Winter (Dec–Mar) &amp; Summer (May–Aug) steelhead 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Best Access Points:</strong> Carver Park, McIver Park, Barton Park, Riverside, Eagle Creek access — excellent for drift-fishing or shore setups 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Techniques:</strong> Swinging flies, drifted roe/yarn rigs, float-plunk method
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    2. <strong>Sandy River</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Distance:</strong> ~35 min east (Gresham/Troutdale)
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Runs:</strong> Winter steelhead (Dec–Apr) and summer fish in spring and early summer 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Prime Access Spots:</strong> Dodge Park, Oxbow, Lewis &amp; Clark SRA for both bank and drift fishing
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tactics:</strong> Drift fishing with bait, swinging flies in deeper pools&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    3. <strong>Willamette River (Below Willamette Falls)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Distance:</strong> ~25 min via OR-43/US-26
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Runs:</strong> Strong winter steelhead runs 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access Spots:</strong> Meldrum Bar (Gladstone), upstream of Clackamas confluence, and near the Fall City falls
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Approach:</strong> Drift, plunk spinners and plugs, euro-nymphing
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    4. <strong>Columbia River (Lower Section)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Distance:</strong> ~40 min (Sauvie Island, Government Island)
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Runs:</strong> Summer steelhead from June through August 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access Options:</strong> Sauvie Island ramps, Reeder Rd, Government Island (boat required for some), beaches near Bonneville Dam 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Method:</strong> Trolling, plunking spinners or bait, swinging flies&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>
